cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE 

The paper focuses on the security and privacy challenges of IoT networks and proposes techniques for profiling the network behavioral pattern of IoTs, automating IoT classification, deducing their operating context, and detecting anomalous behavior indicative of cyber-attacks. This makes it highly likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning-based inference engines for classification and detection, which suggests it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the development of modularized unsupervised inference engines, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
